Guarani: Ñorãirõ ñepyrũme, opavave submarino oikundaha ysyry guasu ári, hakatu radar oñembokatypyryvépe, umi submarino-kuéra oñapymĩma ojehecha’ỹhag̃uãicha. English: In the beginning of the war they mostly travelled on top of the sea, but as radar began developing and becoming more accurate the submarines were forced to go under water to avoid being seen. Guarani: Upécharamo jepe, umi ka’aguy ndaha’éi manglares añónte, oĩ avei ipype rodal ipahápe opytáva ka’aguy guasúpe, ymave ojahao’i va’ekue Ganges llanura. English: The rivers of the Ganges are a source of great water, and the water is used for irrigation.
clean_output: The rivers of the Ganges are a source of great water, and the water is used for irrigation.
